cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.SE 

This paper deals with privacy leakage and detection of suspicious network traffic flows from the user's perspective. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of network traffic and location sharing instances, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a proof-of-concept system, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the paper deals with privacy concerns related to mobile devices, which could also make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
